&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE PRODUCT MANAGER ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WIN is looking for a Product Manager to join our growing team in India. You will work at the&amp;nbsp;intersection of AI, operations, data, and customer experience to build scalable, high-impact&amp;nbsp;products across internal and customer-facing platforms.&amp;nbsp;This is not a Scrum Master or delivery coordination role. This role requires a strong product&amp;nbsp;mindset - someone who can identify opportunities before the market does, translate ambiguity&amp;nbsp;into structured systems, and build products that fundamentally change how people work.&amp;nbsp;You will work across AI-powered workflows, inspection operations, data intelligence, and&amp;nbsp;platform thinking to create products that drive real business outcomes and long-term value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;● Define and drive product strategy for internal and customer-facing platforms&lt;br&gt;● Identify product opportunities across AI, automation, analytics, and workflow optimization&lt;br&gt;● Translate complex and ambiguous business problems into structured product solutions&lt;br&gt;● Collaborate with engineering, design, operations, and leadership to shape product&amp;nbsp;roadmap&lt;br&gt;● Build scalable product systems and frameworks instead of one-off feature solutions&lt;br&gt;● Prioritize initiatives based on impact, adoption, and business outcomes&lt;br&gt;● Leverage data, user research, and experimentation to deeply understand user behaviour&lt;br&gt;● Drive execution with clarity and ownership without acting as a project coordinator&lt;br&gt;● Design AI-first product experiences rather than simply adding AI features&lt;br&gt;● Focus on long-term product value including adoption, retention, efficiency, and&amp;nbsp;ecosystem growth&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;● 4+ years of experience in Product Management or Product Ownership in a product-driven company&lt;br&gt;● Strong understanding of APIs, system integrations, and platform architecture&amp;nbsp;fundamentals&lt;br&gt;● Familiarity with AI/LLM workflows and their practical applications in products&lt;br&gt;● Experience with product analytics, experimentation, and data-driven decision making&lt;br&gt;● Understanding of SaaS product models and workflow automation ecosystems&lt;br&gt;● Ability to work closely with engineering teams and evaluate technical feasibility&lt;br&gt;● Strong problem-solving skills with the ability to simplify complex systems&lt;br&gt;● Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills&lt;br&gt;● Experience working in cross-functional teams in an agile environment&lt;br&gt;● Ownership mindset, curiosity, and bias for action&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GOOD TO HAVE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;● Experience with AI copilots, conversational interfaces, or workflow engines&lt;br&gt;● Exposure to automation tools, predictive analytics, or operational products&lt;br&gt;● Experience building or scaling B2B SaaS platforms&lt;br&gt;● Strong understanding of product-led growth principles&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHY JOIN US?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;● High-energy team enthusiastic about disrupting a massive industry&lt;br&gt;● Highly inclusive and collaborative culture built on mutual respect&lt;br&gt;● Focus on core values, initiative, leadership, and adaptability&lt;br&gt;● Strong emphasis on personal and professional development&lt;br&gt;● Opportunity to build AI-first products that create real business leverage&lt;br&gt;● Flexibility to work remotely&lt;/p&gt;
